public abstract class ExtendedSet<T>
extends java.util.AbstractSet<T>
implements java.util.SortedSet<T>, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<ExtendedSet<T>>

An implementation SortedSet with fast intersection/union/difference and other operations

Version:
1.0
Author:
Alessandro Colantonio, colanton@mat.uniroma3.it, http://ricerca.mat.uniroma3.it/users/colanton
See Also:
ConciseSet, FastSet, IndexedSet

powerSet

public java.util.List<? extends ExtendedSet<T>> powerSet()
Computes the power-set of the current set.

It is a particular implementation of the algorithm Apriori. The power-set does not contains the empty set. The list is sorted according to the lexicographical order provided by the sorted set.

Returns:
the power-set

powerSet

public java.util.List<? extends ExtendedSet<T>> powerSet(int min,
                                                         int max)
Computes a subset of the power-set of the current set, composed by those subsets that have cardinality between min and max.

It is a particular implementation of the algorithm Apriori. The power-set does not contains the empty set. The list is sorted according to the lexicographical order provided by the sorted set.

Parameters:
min - minimum subset size (greater than zero)
max - maximum subset size
Returns:
the power-set
